Tropical Infectious Diseases, 2nd edition
<http://thelancet.url123.com/a5445>

Date: Wed 19 Oct 2005
From: Caroline Brown <CBR@euro.who.int>


WHO/EC support Romania, Bulgaria and Turkey
-----------------------------------------------
A team of 3 experts including a senior epidemiologist from WHO EURO
region, a senior epidemiologist from the ECDC [European Centre for
Disease Prevention and Control] and a veterinary expert from WHO
Geneva are currently in Romania to perform a risk assessment for
avian influenza regarding human and animal health and to discuss
public health response, surveillance and communication issues. The
team is visiting Romania from Sunday 16 Oct 2005 to Thu 20 Oct 2005
and have been sent in response to a request from the Romanian
government. The preliminary findings of the visit will be presented
at a press conference in Bucharest on Thu 20 Oct 2005.

The expert teams sent by the EC to both Bulgaria and Turkey are made
up of 2 veterinary experts, including veterinary epidemiologists.

(Submitted on behalf of the Regional Advisor for Communicable
Diseases, Dr. Bernardus Ganter, WHO EURO Region.)

--
Caroline Brown (CDS-CSR)
Technical Officer
Communicable Disease Surveillance and Response
WHO Regional Office for Europe
Scherfigsvej 8
2100 Copenhagen
Denmark
<CBR@euro.who.int>
